FBIS4-21922 "jptot015__l94087" JPRS-TOT-94-015-L JPRS Terrorism FOUO 7 April 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL `Terrorist' Killed After Opening Fire in Ashdod `Terrorist' Killed After Opening Fire in Ashdod Jihad Also Takes Credit NC0704105994 Paris AFP in English 1010 GMT 7 Apr 94 NC0704105994 Paris AFP English BFN [Text] Al-Shati' refugee camp, Occupied Gaza Strip, April 7 (AFP) -- Islamic Jihad claimed responsibility for shooting dead an Israeli and wounding four others on Wednesday [as received]. "The Islamic Jihad movement mourns with dignity and pride our martyr 'Ali Talib al-'Ammawi, hero of the Ashdod crossing operation," the fundamentalist group said in a statement. The family live in al-Shati' refugee camp on the edge of Gaza City and his father Muhammad told AFP the boy was 19 years old and in his last year at high school. He said his son had supported the fundamentalist movement Islamic Jihad. Al-'Ammawi stepped off a bus at the port city of Ashdod and opened fire on a group of Israelis with an Uzi sub-machinegun, police said.
